WEBVTT

00:46.807 --> 00:48.295
Emergency?

00:54.739 --> 00:55.730
Hello?

00:57.982 --> 00:59.190
What's the problem?

01:00.307 --> 01:01.438
Hello?

01:01.515 --> 01:02.833
Help.

01:07.642 --> 01:08.801
They're sick.

01:13.697 --> 01:15.591
They're all sick.

01:29.718 --> 01:31.971
There's blood..

01:33.366 --> 01:35.964
There's blood..

01:36.084 --> 01:37.346
Everywhere.

01:52.389 --> 01:54.131
They're looking for us.

01:55.318 --> 01:56.117
Please.

02:04.759 --> 02:06.054
Find us.

03:00.830 --> 03:03.028
The incidents in the States
were isolated.

03:03.077 --> 03:04.556
Successfuly contained.

03:04.596 --> 03:06.098
We don't know how
it reached there.

03:06.140 --> 03:09.733
Your inability to manage and contain
this situation is mind boggling.

03:09.765 --> 03:14.461
Let me be frank, under your guidance
we're now standing face to face with a catasrophic shitstorm..

03:14.509 --> 03:17.808
And i am standing face to face
with incompetence.

03:18.008 --> 03:19.039
Translate.

03:19.478 --> 03:20.781
May i have your attention please?

03:21.573 --> 03:23.492
From here on,
the team is small.

03:24.212 --> 03:26.748
No parents,
no family.

03:26.940 --> 03:29.746
Anyone meeting that criteria,
please go the the exits now.

03:31.640 --> 03:34.527
If something's go sideways,
i've never been good in sending flowers.

03:40.331 --> 03:41.250
Pull it up.

03:42.886 --> 03:45.843
Ground Zero was a non-profit housing
for Humanity's Project.

03:45.963 --> 03:48.297
American tourists building shacks
for the poor.

03:48.576 --> 03:50.550
Fatalities were discovered on site.

03:50.814 --> 03:52.230
One anomaly.

03:56.002 --> 03:57.457
The sample arrived this morning.

03:57.497 --> 03:58.448
Bridget..

03:58.657 --> 04:01.646
He's not a sample. He's a patient.
-Yes.

04:02.559 --> 04:04.029
He's Patient Zero.

04:13.702 --> 04:14.590
Mr Porter?

04:16.404 --> 04:17.435
Mr Porter?

04:17.555 --> 04:19.394
My name is Dr. Edwards.

04:47.502 --> 04:48.961
We are..

04:49.081 --> 04:50.869
On the verge..

04:50.989 --> 04:52.761
Of a global pandemic.

04:52.881 --> 04:54.469
And you are..

04:54.589 --> 04:58.971
The only known carrier of this virus
who's asymtopmatic.

04:59.401 --> 05:00.849
The good news..

05:01.129 --> 05:03.666
Is that it's not an airborne virus.

05:03.686 --> 05:05.384
And the bad news is..

05:05.504 --> 05:07.482
We have no way
of containing it.

05:08.957 --> 05:10.625
Where is my son?

05:11.624 --> 05:13.697
We're supposed to go somewhere.

05:13.817 --> 05:15.195
His prep school.

05:15.535 --> 05:18.667
We have to buy books
and pencils.

05:20.485 --> 05:22.673
Your son is dead, Mr Porter.

05:22.963 --> 05:24.366
I think you know that.

05:33.293 --> 05:35.020
You have..

05:35.559 --> 05:37.747
An incredible
opportunity.

05:37.867 --> 05:40.005
To do something special.

05:42.026 --> 05:43.615
I can't help you.

05:46.337 --> 05:47.986
I wasn't asking.

05:49.005 --> 05:51.104
I don't know who the fuck
you think you are..

06:29.163 --> 06:30.751
There he is.
There he is.

06:31.171 --> 06:32.300
Yeah.

06:32.420 --> 06:34.759
Hey, friend!
-Hey!

06:38.164 --> 06:39.642
What's up, bro?

06:40.811 --> 06:43.023
What the hell
are you wearing?

06:43.233 --> 06:46.290
What do you mean?
Kate wants me to look sophisticated.

06:46.550 --> 06:48.425
What's so funny?

06:48.855 --> 06:50.513
Why were you so late?

06:50.633 --> 06:52.769
Oh the transportation,
they ran a little late.

06:52.889 --> 06:55.097
I got like an extra $600 on them, though.

06:55.117 --> 06:57.634
Really?
-What do you think? It's about time we..

06:57.894 --> 07:03.217
Do the whole 30 footer boat,
maybe expand the dive shot?

07:03.337 --> 07:07.210
Let's talk business after the wedding, let me just get through this first, alright?
-Alright.

07:07.240 --> 07:10.741
We're late, we're so late.
Kate's whole family is waiting for us.

07:11.221 --> 07:13.269
Come on, we gotta get going.

07:13.389 --> 07:14.819
I'm glad you can make it.

07:14.939 --> 07:18.375
What do you mean, glad i can make it?
Marky, look at me.

07:18.735 --> 07:21.504
I wouldn't miss this
for the world, brother. Alright?

07:34.942 --> 07:37.169
Bro, this one's taken.

07:40.346 --> 07:41.994
So rude.

07:43.513 --> 07:46.674
To Marcus' brother,
wherever he's hiding.

07:46.794 --> 07:48.552
A warm thank you.

07:48.812 --> 07:52.605
And i'd like to offer a special toast
to those who couldn't be here tonight.

07:52.635 --> 07:54.613
Marcus' parents.

07:55.053 --> 07:56.452
They'll be dearly missed.

08:07.688 --> 08:09.447
You're the guy, buddy.
You're the guy.

08:10.396 --> 08:13.834
Marcus, you promised.
-Promise what?

08:15.312 --> 08:18.829
Oh no.. What is he wearing?

08:19.469 --> 08:21.040
Wait one second.

08:21.420 --> 08:23.678
I'll take care of this.
I'll be right back.

08:26.026 --> 08:28.811
Alright, who ate all the food?

08:30.070 --> 08:31.668
This guy.

08:31.788 --> 08:33.787
Hey Josh..
-Hey.

08:35.296 --> 08:37.335
Come on, i think you've had enough.

08:38.005 --> 08:40.134
Hola.
-Hey.

08:40.683 --> 08:42.523
Hey Marky, long time.

08:42.643 --> 08:44.011
Penny..

08:46.592 --> 08:47.691
What?

08:51.456 --> 08:55.672
Guys, guys come on.
There's water right there.

08:56.362 --> 08:59.619
What happened to the shirt i left out for you?
And the pants?

09:00.518 --> 09:02.930
Dude, this looks really cool.

09:04.898 --> 09:06.766
Is it good?
Good food?

09:06.886 --> 09:08.211
Aloha.

09:08.331 --> 09:11.697
Go, go,
go get your lady, man.

09:12.906 --> 09:14.575
This is pretty.

09:27.229 --> 09:30.783
We're gonna..
Why don't we get some fresh oranges?

09:40.917 --> 09:42.855
Very lucky man..
How do i say lucky man?

09:47.684 --> 09:49.043
Helo, friend.

09:49.822 --> 09:51.117
What's up?

10:04.929 --> 10:06.338
No, thank you.

10:17.836 --> 10:20.683
She's not trying to sell it to you,
she's trying to give it to you.

10:22.202 --> 10:25.447
It's a Puka.

10:25.737 --> 10:28.184
It's for protection,
against evil.

10:28.843 --> 10:30.561
From..
Santeria.

10:30.661 --> 10:32.589
Like a..

10:32.689 --> 10:34.627
Central America voodoo thing.

10:34.647 --> 10:37.624
Beheaded chickens,
sacrifices..

10:38.293 --> 10:40.239
Gotta love the third world.

10:51.106 --> 10:52.165
Marky..

10:52.395 --> 10:54.143
Yo, check that one.

10:55.558 --> 10:57.227
Yeah, not too shabby.

10:57.347 --> 10:59.025
Why don't you take it
for a test drive?

10:59.055 --> 11:01.549
Yeah right.
-Hello, friends.

11:01.759 --> 11:03.307
Marky Marcus..

11:03.846 --> 11:05.345
Your brother and i..

11:05.375 --> 11:09.037
Your two best..
Your two lifers..

11:09.157 --> 11:14.110
Your two fuck ups, who couldn't afford
a real bachelor party back home..

11:14.340 --> 11:16.438
Have conspired to pull this off.

11:17.314 --> 11:19.402
Bro, we've been planning this
for months.

11:19.522 --> 11:22.209
One last night of freedom
with the old crew.

11:22.279 --> 11:25.340
And a charterred trip to a deserted
tropical island.

11:25.460 --> 11:28.467
Full of beers, suns,
and virgin bitches..

11:28.587 --> 11:30.205
Beaches..
-Beaches.

11:30.325 --> 11:31.674
Sand, water..

11:36.154 --> 11:38.371
For real?
-Have a good time, babe.

11:41.122 --> 11:45.450
Wait a sec, so all that crap
about no bachelor party?

11:45.570 --> 11:47.208
Was prep..

11:48.447 --> 11:51.695
Hey man, hotel already loaded our bags.
-No..

11:51.815 --> 11:53.603
No..

11:54.454 --> 11:57.660
Don't forget to wear sunscreen,
i don't want you sunburned in all the photos tomorrow.

11:57.780 --> 12:00.515
I won't.
-And do not go too far north.

12:00.635 --> 12:02.433
It's restricted waters.

12:02.692 --> 12:05.100
Hey, if you're so worried,
why don't you come?

12:05.220 --> 12:07.532
It wouldn't be a bachelor party
if i'm there.

12:08.381 --> 12:10.080
Why is Penny going?

12:12.742 --> 12:15.839
She's practically one of the guys,
you guys grew up together.

12:15.959 --> 12:19.254
Besides, my family is having
this thing for me tonight and..

12:19.374 --> 12:21.478
It'll be terribly stiff
and proper.

12:21.748 --> 12:24.196
She'd be miserable.
-Would she?

12:25.015 --> 12:27.335
It's easier on all of us.

12:27.455 --> 12:29.642
Go have a good time,
you deserve it.

12:29.762 --> 12:31.391
You're a horrible liar.

12:40.093 --> 12:41.431
You're beautiful.

12:42.429 --> 12:43.618
I'll miss you.

12:47.314 --> 12:49.522
Bye.
-Okay..

12:49.642 --> 12:51.171
There he is.
-Okay.

12:51.291 --> 12:52.889
Yeah!
-Okay.

12:54.372 --> 12:57.798
Let's keep it adjusted.
Tune time, tune time.

13:15.803 --> 13:18.300
Three blind mice..

13:18.420 --> 13:21.022
Three blind mice..

13:21.142 --> 13:23.789
See how they run..

13:39.152 --> 13:41.240
My mother used to sing
that to me.

13:42.059 --> 13:44.028
I love children's songs.

13:44.967 --> 13:46.995
Your children song
is a protest..

13:47.115 --> 13:51.137
Against the wrongful imprisonment,
torture and execution of three Protestans..

13:51.157 --> 13:53.191
By Queen Mary
in the 1500s.

13:53.311 --> 13:55.169
Porter, please.

13:56.148 --> 13:58.907
You can't go days without
talking to anyone.

13:59.027 --> 14:00.995
Please, talk to me.

14:01.464 --> 14:03.013
Oh, you want to talk?

14:03.512 --> 14:04.695
Okay.

14:05.145 --> 14:06.803
How's my wife?

14:08.861 --> 14:10.401
Does she know
i'm here?

14:11.101 --> 14:12.639
She knows about
her son?

14:14.979 --> 14:16.927
Does she know
that he melted in my arms?

14:18.306 --> 14:19.754
Does she?

14:19.874 --> 14:20.631
Porter, stop.

14:20.751 --> 14:23.808
They all ran after the farmer's wife,
and cut off their tails with a carving knife..

14:23.928 --> 14:26.786
Porter, stop!
Don't put yourself through this.

14:27.406 --> 14:28.934
Please.

14:29.151 --> 14:31.809
I'm a US citizen,
i have rights.

14:32.138 --> 14:34.888
I want to talk to the
American Embassy.

14:35.008 --> 14:38.475
It's the US CDC law that requires
that you'd be quarantined.

14:38.844 --> 14:40.641
You're a pandemic carrier.

14:40.761 --> 14:42.239
We're not in
United States.

14:42.359 --> 14:44.047
This is extraordinary rendition..

14:44.167 --> 14:46.593
You can't just keep
experimenting on me!

14:46.713 --> 14:49.590
Porter, you're not just
a carrier.

14:50.399 --> 14:52.588
You're a possible cure.

14:52.987 --> 14:55.325
You have a natural imunity
to the virus.

14:55.445 --> 14:57.781
Try to focus on the good
that you're providing.

14:57.811 --> 14:59.699
I've complied to everything
you've wanted.

14:59.819 --> 15:01.935
You've poked and prodded on me
for two months.

15:02.055 --> 15:03.983
If i don't talk to my wife
in the next 15 minutes..

15:04.036 --> 15:07.065
I swear to God, i'm gonna kill myself.
Do you hear me?

15:07.185 --> 15:09.291
I'm gonna fucking
kill myself!

15:09.315 --> 15:11.090
I've spoken with Christina.

15:14.904 --> 15:15.896
Porter.

15:16.141 --> 15:18.133
She knows about your son.

15:22.295 --> 15:25.426
She also knows that you are here with us
in quarantine.

15:25.907 --> 15:28.017
Obviously she's worried about you.

15:29.409 --> 15:32.280
She wanted me to tell you
that she loves you very much.

15:34.652 --> 15:36.213
And she'll be waiting for you.

15:53.803 --> 15:55.499
I want you to know something.

15:57.432 --> 15:59.636
I'm not just dangerous to myself.

16:17.931 --> 16:19.821
They are remarkable specimens.

16:19.941 --> 16:21.087
Human.

16:21.207 --> 16:24.463
You mean human, don't you doctor?
He's a human being.

16:26.835 --> 16:28.616
Get up, come on.

16:35.683 --> 16:38.577
What we have in that cage
isn't just a man.

16:38.697 --> 16:40.495
It is the engine of a new
life form..

16:40.549 --> 16:43.175
And make no mistake,
it wants to destroy us.

16:43.991 --> 16:46.573
Don't personalize this,
Camila.

16:47.020 --> 16:50.196
Sometimes we have to
harm one..

16:50.230 --> 16:52.340
In order to save millions.

17:25.255 --> 17:27.622
The sample's in the ready position, doctor.

17:27.742 --> 17:30.205
Good morning, Mr Porter.
It's time for your 8.30.

17:30.593 --> 17:32.539
Jorge, prepare for another extraction.

17:32.573 --> 17:34.885
Mark it 0713.

17:35.005 --> 17:39.652
Bridget, i'll need a full work up
on the genome and the basic protein.

18:19.881 --> 18:21.511
Don't you get up, Mr Porter.

18:21.545 --> 18:22.659
Don't you move.

18:22.779 --> 18:25.165
It's my blood you want, right?
You want it?

18:25.285 --> 18:26.293
Take it!

18:29.559 --> 18:32.565
You want to shoot me?
Come on, shoot!

18:41.368 --> 18:42.372
Wait!

18:42.492 --> 18:43.857
This is a mistake.

18:43.977 --> 18:46.153
The situation has been contained.
-Hello?

18:46.273 --> 18:47.678
The sample is still secure.

18:47.798 --> 18:49.670
I'm sorry, Doctor.
As you know..

18:49.712 --> 18:54.164
The protocol requires a mandatory facility lockdown of 48 hours.

18:54.805 --> 18:59.221
All of the staff will be temporarily transferred
to the evacuation bunker.

18:59.263 --> 19:01.837
Where we wait for
re-entry clearance.

19:02.462 --> 19:04.694
I'm sure you understand.

19:07.352 --> 19:09.806
We will see you in two days.

19:42.190 --> 19:43.262
Friend.

19:48.009 --> 19:50.929
You always had the biggest crush on her
back in second grade.

19:51.049 --> 19:52.581
You never want to admit it.

19:52.631 --> 19:54.843
So when's the last time
you saw Penny anyway?

19:57.435 --> 20:00.228
Alright, on your feet soldiers!

20:00.532 --> 20:02.068
Come on!

20:04.358 --> 20:06.620
Alright boys, man up.

20:06.662 --> 20:08.463
Open up your hatches on 3.

20:08.506 --> 20:10.548
1.. 2.. 3.

20:21.620 --> 20:23.899
Come on, you're the one who taught me
how to do this.

20:23.935 --> 20:25.640
Yeah, when i was 19.

20:25.690 --> 20:27.209
Now i drink for flavor.

20:27.766 --> 20:29.873
Oh yeah, that's for babies.

20:29.923 --> 20:32.202
He's all fancy now that
he's marrying into money.

20:32.252 --> 20:34.556
Hey, hey..
Jokes aside..

20:35.206 --> 20:36.962
Marky Marcus.

20:37.082 --> 20:39.131
As your little bro
and best friend.

20:39.738 --> 20:42.278
Tomorrow night when you wed
the lovely Kate..

20:42.398 --> 20:45.620
The single world will mourn the loss
of one of the greats.

20:46.164 --> 20:47.565
And in honor of that..

20:47.685 --> 20:51.515
I got you something meaningful
to help prepare you for a new life.

20:51.536 --> 20:53.604
What is this, Joshie?
What did you get me?

20:54.186 --> 20:55.739
What is this?

20:56.237 --> 20:58.898
Oh, is this about that thing?

20:58.931 --> 21:02.037
Open it.
-What could this be?

21:08.264 --> 21:09.834
Boom!
-Boom!

21:11.024 --> 21:14.205
Thanks guys, i can take care
of my girl.

21:14.230 --> 21:19.039
It's not for her, that's for you.
Getting you all loosen up for all the bend over you'll be doing.

21:19.081 --> 21:21.757
I told these boners
they were crossing the line.

21:21.799 --> 21:23.166
Alright, it's my turn.

21:24.173 --> 21:25.987
But mine needs an explanation.

21:26.916 --> 21:31.454
Do you remember when we were kids
and you went to go inside the Street Lamp Charade?

21:31.574 --> 21:32.822
Yeah.

21:33.319 --> 21:35.233
What is it?
-Open it.

21:36.110 --> 21:37.680
So you always know
where you came from.

21:37.800 --> 21:39.309
Oh wow..
-Watch.

21:40.264 --> 21:42.830
That's awesome, thank you so much, Pen.

21:43.378 --> 21:44.670
It's so cool.

21:49.671 --> 21:50.566
Alright.

21:50.686 --> 21:52.743
This is your own present.

21:57.493 --> 21:59.417
No, fuck no.
-Woo Woo..

21:59.501 --> 22:01.417
Hey hey.. We spent a fortune on that.

22:01.451 --> 22:04.379
You guys know how much trouble we're gonna get
if the Coast Guard finds this on here?

22:04.738 --> 22:07.785
Not to mention Kate's family,
how embarassed they'll be guys.

22:07.905 --> 22:09.525
God forbid that happens.

22:09.645 --> 22:11.391
Mark, Mark..

22:12.783 --> 22:15.007
We've been going north
for a while now.

22:15.127 --> 22:17.826
We haven't seen a boat in 2 hours.

22:19.007 --> 22:20.154
Hey, hey..

22:20.914 --> 22:25.098
Think we're far enough away from civilization
where you can relax a little bit, maybe..

22:25.218 --> 22:26.373
Let loose?

22:27.166 --> 22:29.992
Yeah, yeah.
-There we go. It's that kid..

22:30.034 --> 22:32.659
There he is, come here.

22:33.115 --> 22:35.694
Firing up from Kate's
scornful lies.

22:36.191 --> 22:38.917
Stop with the comments about Kate, please.

22:38.951 --> 22:40.202
It's just a joke, bro.

22:40.236 --> 22:42.582
No, you don't like her.
I get it.

22:43.485 --> 22:46.084
Now shut up, because after tomorrow night..

22:47.324 --> 22:48.886
That's my wife
you're talking about.

22:49.671 --> 22:52.867
Marky Mark, come on dude.
Hey!

22:54.176 --> 22:55.062
What?

22:55.182 --> 22:57.291
When you get married,
you can't take a joke anymore?

23:02.724 --> 23:04.218
You see what's going on, right?

23:05.096 --> 23:07.046
They're scared that you're marrying up.

23:07.868 --> 23:09.657
And you'll gonna leave them behind.

23:11.109 --> 23:13.330
I'm not gonna leave
them behind.

23:14.605 --> 23:16.664
What's wrong with wanting more
than what you grew up with?

23:16.698 --> 23:17.812
Nothing.

23:18.833 --> 23:20.555
If that's what you really want.

23:25.001 --> 23:26.470
Is it?
-Penny..

23:28.816 --> 23:29.879
What do you want?

23:30.470 --> 23:32.178
Penny, come on.
That's not the..

23:32.298 --> 23:34.541
That's not the point,
Kate gets me.

23:36.027 --> 23:38.297
She's not like the people
we grew up with.

23:42.547 --> 23:43.922
And what's wrong with us?

23:47.390 --> 23:48.538
Nothing.

23:49.601 --> 23:51.433
Kate just sees more for me.

23:52.652 --> 23:55.404
There was a time when you told me
something similar.

23:56.653 --> 23:58.249
Penny, we were kids.

23:59.532 --> 24:00.536
Funny.

24:00.798 --> 24:03.302
I remember doing some
pretty adult things.

24:03.682 --> 24:06.839
Hey, hey, come on.
You're with Josh now.

24:06.959 --> 24:08.425
Josh is fun.

24:08.900 --> 24:10.690
But not serious.

24:11.156 --> 24:13.707
Kate's serious,
but not fun.

24:14.845 --> 24:16.895
Maybe we both made
the wrong choice.

24:17.439 --> 24:19.041
It was one summer.

24:21.828 --> 24:23.879
Don't make it more
than it was.

24:26.382 --> 24:28.506
Sorry, gotta get..
Gotta go.

24:33.721 --> 24:35.977
Hey, she blows..

24:36.097 --> 24:37.594
Check it out.

24:40.809 --> 24:43.403
That's the deserted paradise, huh?

24:44.271 --> 24:46.104
It's Never Neverland, Marky.

24:46.574 --> 24:47.824
It's not even on the map.

24:49.301 --> 24:50.337
So..

24:51.146 --> 24:51.935
Is that..

24:52.994 --> 24:55.808
Is that a building on the northern side
of the ridge over there?

24:56.301 --> 24:57.400
What bui..
What?

24:59.448 --> 25:03.435
Hey, it's supposed to be virgin beach,
understand?

25:03.686 --> 25:06.303
No.. No people.

25:06.423 --> 25:08.065
No building.

25:14.569 --> 25:15.730
What does that mean?

